The paper deals with video capture and reconstruction using compressive sensing and sparse reconstruction techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional sparse coding (CSC), which is a technique commonly used in signal processing and image analysis (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the optimization of the CSC algorithm, which is a topic commonly studied in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of sparsity constraints, which is a topic commonly studied in neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE).
